comment:
* This class specifies the set of parameters used for generating * Diffie-Hellman (system) parameters for use in Diffie-Hellman key * agreement. This is typically done by a central * authority. * *

The central authority, after computing the parameters, must send this * information to the parties looking to agree on a secret key. * * @author Jan Luehe * * @see DHParameterSpec * @since 1.4

variables.name: primeSize
variables.comment: The size in bits of the prime modulus

variables.name: exponentSize
variables.comment: The size in bits of the random exponent (private value)

methods.name: public int getPrimeSize()
methods.comment:
* Returns the size in bits of the prime modulus.
     *
     * @return the size in bits of the prime modulus

methods.name: public int getExponentSize()
methods.comment:
* Returns the size in bits of the random exponent (private value).
     *
     * @return the size in bits of the random exponent (private value)
